			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Only idiots get hit by bolts...<br><br>But besides that,<br>On PvP servers most battles occur in places with lots of hills where bolts aren't that effective anyway.  (Most of the highly contested areas just seem to be very hilly.)<br><br>Furthermore, most of the time your epic pet is between you and them (since they are probably running away from you, and EVERYONE runs from the epic pet.) and will get hit by the bolt instead of them.<br><br>Also, on PvP servers people don't stand still and let you cast spells on them that often.  Since they are almost certainately moving if you cast a bolt at extreme range, more likely than not by the time your slow casting bolt spell goes off you will get the &quot;Target is out of range&quot; message.<br> <p></p><i></i></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
