			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I applaud our new pvp mage for taking the effort to experience something new. At the same, I would caution you to draw comparisons between your lowbie pvp experiences and pre-level 57-65 experiences.
<br />

<br />
Pre-50, I think mages absolutely kick the hell out of most other classes all things being equal. Post 50, and especially post 60, things get a bit trickier as far as where the mage falls relative to his peers.
<br />

<br />
My hope is that you begin to level on your pvp server and see a bit more of the experience. Get involved in guilds and learn some of nuances of mass pvp at higher levels. With these experiences, you will be better able to draw some more viable conclusions.<br />_________________<br /><span style="color: red"><span style="font-weight: bold">Sage Svenuce Summonstuff</span></span>
<br />
Arch Convoker of Vallon Zek
<br />
Officer of <a href="http://www.zephyrosguild.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Zephyros</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
