				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well speaking from experience (sorry 20 min on a pvp server does not count my friend) it IS our class that is hindering us from pvp. Kryptopholus and I (guildmates) are both avid pvpers and we can tell you mages would get a huge overhaul if SoE gave a rats ass about pvp.
<br />
Pre-50 (or at 52- with epic) mages are god plain and simple. When you fight time geared people however, that all changes. Mage nukes do not land. Fire pet for pvp (even if it chained lure) would do pretty much nothing against people rocking 30% spell shield.... and rune... and bulwark. Your best bets for pvp on a mage in general are:
<br />

<br />
Dispell - Learn it, use it, love it
<br />
Speed/surprise- if you're opponent doesnt know you are coming and cant get ready ( get a pet, organize buffs, ++ faction spell guards) you have a huge advantage
<br />
Horse- get ready to do alot of running
<br />
Resists- only way to beat the other 3 caster classes (and sk spears bard dots) is to resist their nukes and make them go oom
<br />
Levi- if levi would give you an advantage against somone, use it
<br />

<br />
I don't have MS4 yet but if the bull rush stun is indeed unresistable it might give us at least a fighting chance against classes like cleric and druid<br />_________________<br />65 Arch Convoker
<br />
Rallos Zek
<br />
Wudan
<br />

